Note:
Runa Type Inference Implementation Tests: Comprehensive Test Suite

This test suite validates the Hindley-Milner type inference implementation.
It tests the core unification algorithm, constraint solving, and type inference for various expressions.

Test Coverage:
- Type unification with occurs check
- Constraint solving and substitution
- Type inference for literals, variables, and expressions
- Function type inference
- Generic type handling
- Error reporting and diagnostics
- Performance metrics
:End Note

Note: Import test dependencies
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/type_inference.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/diagnostics.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/semantic/symbol_table.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/parser/ast.runa"

Note: Test Suite Configuration
Let test_config be dictionary containing:
    "verbose" as true
    "stop_on_failure" as false
    "performance_tracking" as true

Note: Test Results Tracking
Let test_results be dictionary containing:
    "total_tests" as 0
    "passed_tests" as 0
    "failed_tests" as 0
    "performance_metrics" as dictionary containing

Note: Test 1: Type Inference Engine Creation
Process called "test_inference_engine_creation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that type inference engine can be created
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Note: Verify engine structure
        Assert inference_engine.type_variables is not None
        Assert inference_engine.constraints is not None
        Assert inference_engine.substitution is not None
        Assert inference_engine.current_scope is equal to "global"
        Assert inference_engine.generalization_level is equal to 0
        Assert inference_engine.performance_metrics is not None
        Assert inference_engine.diagnostic_engine is equal to diagnostic_engine
        
        Note: Verify performance metrics structure
        Let metrics be inference_engine.performance_metrics
        Assert metrics.unifications is equal to 0
        Assert metrics.generalizations is equal to 0
        Assert metrics.instantiations is equal to 0
        Assert metrics.constraint_solves is equal to 0
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 1: Type Inference Engine Creation - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 1: Type Inference Engine Creation - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 2: Primitive Type Unification
Process called "test_primitive_type_unification" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test unification of primitive types
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let type1 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
        Let type2 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
        
        Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as type1 and type2 as type2
        
        Note: Verify successful unification
        Assert result.success is equal to true
        Assert length of result.errors is equal to 0
        Assert length of result.substitution is equal to 0
        
        Note: Test incompatible types
        Let type3 be create_primitive_type with name as "String"
        Let result2 be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as type1 and type2 as type3
        
        Assert result2.success is equal to false
        Assert length of result2.errors is greater than 0
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 2: Primitive Type Unification - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 2: Primitive Type Unification - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 3: Type Variable Unification
Process called "test_type_variable_unification" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test unification with type variables
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let var_type be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "T"
        Let number_type be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
        
        Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as var_type and type2 as number_type
        
        Note: Verify successful unification
        Assert result.success is equal to true
        Assert length of result.substitution is equal to 1
        Assert result.substitution at key "T" is equal to number_type
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 3: Type Variable Unification - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 3: Type Variable Unification - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 4: Function Type Unification
Process called "test_function_type_unification" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test unification of function types
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let func1 be create_function_type with parameter_types as list containing create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and return_type as create_primitive_type with name as "String"
        Let func2 be create_function_type with parameter_types as list containing create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and return_type as create_primitive_type with name as "String"
        
        Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as func1 and type2 as func2
        
        Note: Verify successful unification
        Assert result.success is equal to true
        Assert length of result.errors is equal to 0
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 4: Function Type Unification - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 4: Function Type Unification - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 5: Constraint Solving
Process called "test_constraint_solving" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test constraint solving algorithm
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let constraint be create_type_constraint with left as create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and right as create_primitive_type with name as "Number" and location as create_mock_location and context as "test"
        Add constraint to inference_engine.constraints
        
        Let result be solve_constraints with context as inference_engine
        
        Note: Verify successful constraint solving
        Assert result.success is equal to true
        Assert length of result.errors is equal to 0
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 5: Constraint Solving - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 5: Constraint Solving - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 6: Type Inference for Literals
Process called "test_literal_type_inference" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test type inference for literal expressions
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Note: Test numeric literal
        Let numeric_node be ASTNode with:
            type as "Literal"
            line as 1
            column as 1
            location as create_mock_location
            value as "42"
            literal_type as "integer"
        
        Let visitor be create_type_inference_visitor with context as inference_engine
        Let context be dictionary containing "inference_context" as inference_engine
        
        Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as numeric_node and context as context
        
        Match result:
            When Success with result as inferred_type and context_updates as updates:
                Assert inferred_type.name is equal to "Number"
            When Failure with diagnostics as diagnostics and warnings as warnings:
                Assert false
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 6: Literal Type Inference - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 6: Literal Type Inference - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 7: Type Inference for Binary Operations
Process called "test_binary_operation_inference" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test type inference for binary operations
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Note: Create binary operation AST
        Let binary_node be ASTNode with:
            type as "BinaryOperation"
            line as 1
            column as 1
            location as create_mock_location
            operator as "plus"
            left as ASTNode with:
                type as "Literal"
                line as 1
                column as 1
                location as create_mock_location
                value as "5"
                literal_type as "integer"
            right as ASTNode with:
                type as "Literal"
                line as 1
                column as 5
                location as create_mock_location
                value as "3"
                literal_type as "integer"
        
        Let visitor be create_type_inference_visitor with context as inference_engine
        Let context be dictionary containing "inference_context" as inference_engine
        
        Let result be visit_ast with visitor as visitor and node as binary_node and context as context
        
        Match result:
            When Success with result as inferred_type and context_updates as updates:
                Assert inferred_type.name is equal to "Number"
            When Failure with diagnostics as diagnostics and warnings as warnings:
                Assert false
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 7: Binary Operation Inference - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 7: Binary Operation Inference - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 8: Type Generalization and Instantiation
Process called "test_type_generalization_instantiation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test type generalization and instantiation
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let type_var be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "T"
        Let function_type be create_function_type with parameter_types as list containing type_var and return_type as type_var
        
        Note: Test generalization
        Let generalized_type be generalize_type with context as inference_engine and type as function_type
        Assert generalized_type.kind is equal to "generic"
        
        Note: Test instantiation
        Let instantiated_type be instantiate_type with context as inference_engine and type as generalized_type
        Assert instantiated_type.kind is equal to "function"
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 8: Type Generalization/Instantiation - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 8: Type Generalization/Instantiation - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 9: Occurs Check
Process called "test_occurs_check" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test occurs check for preventing infinite types
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Let var_type be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "T"
        
        Note: Test occurs check with self-reference
        Let occurs_result be occurs_check with context as inference_engine and var_name as "T" and type as var_type
        Assert occurs_result is equal to true
        
        Note: Test occurs check with different variable
        Let other_var be create_fresh_type_variable with context as inference_engine and name as "U"
        Let occurs_result2 be occurs_check with context as inference_engine and var_name as "T" and type as other_var
        Assert occurs_result2 is equal to false
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 9: Occurs Check - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 9: Occurs Check - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Test 10: Performance Metrics
Process called "test_performance_metrics" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test performance metrics tracking
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Try:
        Let diagnostic_engine be create_semantic_diagnostic_engine with max_errors as 100 and max_warnings as 200
        Let inference_engine be create_type_inference_engine with diagnostic_engine as diagnostic_engine
        
        Note: Perform some operations to generate metrics
        Let type1 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
        Let type2 be create_primitive_type with name as "Number"
        Let result be unify_types with context as inference_engine and type1 as type1 and type2 as type2
        
        Let metrics be get_inference_performance_metrics with context as inference_engine
        
        Note: Verify metrics were updated
        Assert metrics.unifications is greater than 0
        Assert metrics.constraint_solves is equal to 0  Note: No constraints added
        
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "✅ Test 10: Performance Metrics - PASSED"
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Print "❌ Test 10: Performance Metrics - FAILED: " plus error.message
        Return false

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "create_mock_location" returns SourceLocation:
    Note: Create a mock source location for testing
    Return SourceLocation with:
        file_path as "test.runa"
        line as 1
        column as 1

Process called "create_function_type" that takes parameter_types as List[RunaType] and return_type as RunaType returns RunaType:
    Note: Create a function type for testing
    Return RunaType with:
        kind as "function"
        name as "Function"
        parameters as parameter_types
        return_type as return_type
        constraints as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Main Test Runner
Process called "run_type_inference_implementation_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Run all type inference implementation tests
    Print "🚀 Starting Runa Type Inference Implementation Test Suite"
    Print "========================================================="
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    
    Note: Run all tests
    Let test1_result be test_inference_engine_creation
    Let test2_result be test_primitive_type_unification
    Let test3_result be test_type_variable_unification
    Let test4_result be test_function_type_unification
    Let test5_result be test_constraint_solving
    Let test6_result be test_literal_type_inference
    Let test7_result be test_binary_operation_inference
    Let test8_result be test_type_generalization_instantiation
    Let test9_result be test_occurs_check
    Let test10_result be test_performance_metrics
    
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    Set test_results.performance_metrics.total_time_ms to end_time minus start_time
    
    Note: Calculate success rate
    Let success_rate be (test_results.passed_tests divided by test_results.total_tests) multiplied by 100
    
    Note: Print results
    Print ""
    Print "📊 Type Inference Test Results Summary"
    Print "======================================"
    Print "Total Tests: " plus test_results.total_tests
    Print "Passed: " plus test_results.passed_tests
    Print "Failed: " plus test_results.failed_tests
    Print "Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    Print "Total Time: " plus test_results.performance_metrics.total_time_ms plus "ms"
    
    If success_rate is equal to 100:
        Print ""
        Print "🎉 ALL TESTS PASSED! Hindley-Milner type inference is ready for production."
    Otherwise:
        Print ""
        Print "⚠️  Some tests failed. Review implementation before proceeding."
    
    Return test_results

Note: Run tests if this file is executed directly
If __name__ is equal to "__main__":
    Let results be run_type_inference_implementation_tests
    Exit with code as (if results.passed_tests is equal to results.total_tests then 0 else 1) 